ELUSIVE CLASS got bumped and impeded leaving the gate, traveled near the back early on, angled in around the bend and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR PROSPECT rated near the inside then in the two path, pulled a bit early on the backstretch, bid outside the leader with three furlongs left to run, took over at the five-sixteenths then kicked clear around the bend, urged a few times right handed entering the stretch and widened through the lane while coasting in the final sixteenth. GHOSTLY ACT sped to the front from inside, cleared outer rivals around the clubhouse turn, showed the way to the second bend, lost command at the five-sixteenths pole, chased the winner into the stretch and churned on down the lane to save the place. BRONKO NAGURSKI pressed from outside into the clubhouse turn then was coaxed along when losing touch with the leader around the bend, remained closest in pursuit up the backstretch while coaxed, asked two to three wide on the final turn, kept to task down the lane while moving to the inside and missed the place. J D'S RUDE BOY stalked three deep early, three to four wide on the far turn and had little left for the drive. HERECOMEGEORGIEBOY chased three to four wide at the back on the clubhouse turn, went four wide into the second bend, came five wide into the stretch, eased in the lane and walked off. RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUTRIGHT tracked along the three path early, moved out and took closer order four deep in the middle stages, bid four wide on the far turn, drew alongside the leader while drifting inward and drove clear. NO HANG CHARLIE sped to the front and moved inward, was challenged from inside and dueled up the backstretch, inched ahead nearing the far turn, showed the way into the final furlong, then yielded to the winner in the final sixteenth. LOOKIN FOR REVENGE chased along the rail early then went up to challenge leaving the first turn, dueled up the backstretch, failed to keep up on the second bend, continued to give chase within range through the drive and kept on to secure the show. BOTTLE OF SMOKE forwardly placed three deep into the clubhouse turn, remained outside the top pair in the middle stages, chased three wide into the lane and flattened. KING OF SPEED raced up close between rivals early then chased leaving the first turn, coaxed along up the backstretch, lost ground on the far turn, tired in the lane, bled following the race and was vanned off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOLD ENDEAVOR stalked two wide early then moved out on the backstretch, bid four deep with a quarter mile remaining, took over into the stretch, dueled with CLUB ASPEN in the furlong grounds and gamely prevailed. CLUB ASPEN pressed the leader from outside while in-hand early, chased three wide into the far turn, challenged three deep late on the bend, dueled inside BOLD ENDEAVOR down the stretch and finished gamely to the wire. ROYAL ACT bobbled leaving the gate, trailed three wide around the clubhouse turn then was taken out wider on the backstretch, rounded the far turn five wide, then came with a late run and gained the show. MIDNIGHT MAMMOTH showed keen early speed while being pressed from outside, dueled outside a rival in the middle stages and lost command at the half-mile pole, vied between foes into the stretch, got put in a bit tight and shuffled in upper stretch and kept on for a minor award. ORDER AND LAW raced near the back on the inside, angled four wide on the far turn, churned on down the lane but needed to find more late. BALADI broke a step slow then lost his path shortly after and had to pause momentarily, chased two wide off the pace around the clubhouse turn, pulled the rider along and went up to engage the leader on the backstretch, took over at the half-mile pole, cleared briefly on the far turn then fought with outside trio into the lane and weakened.
